A 300 Level student of the Department of Microbiology, Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife in Osun State, Akorede Kayode Omotola, on Friday, slumped and died while playing football with other students on campus. Eyewitnesses said he slumped on the football pitch during a match and that he was rushed to the university’s health center but he died before getting to the clinic. The Public Relations Officer of the University, Abiodun Olarewaju, in a telephone chat with Daily Trust, confirmed the death of the student. The PRO said management of the university was sad over the demise of the student. Olarewaju said: “He was rushed to the University Health Centre where he was confirmed dead on arrival. All measures to resuscitate him proved abortive.” Armed robbers kill OAU student in hostel Pupil slumps, dies playing football in Kubwa FUT clinic torched as students protest colleague’s death Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin